						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Snaer wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Are there any "cycle 341"? If one scanline is 341 cycles then the last one should be 340, right?</div><br /><br />- Right. You count 0,1,2...340.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">and what does "2nd or 3rd <span style="text-decoration: underline">byte</span> of a LDA $2002" mean?</div>
<br />
<br />- LDA = 1 byte (3 ppu clocks)
<br />- 02 = +1 byte (3 ppu clocks)
<br />- 20 = +1 byte (3 ppu clocks)
<br />
<br />- The VBlank can rise during the last 6 ppu cycles. I hope to not be taking a wrong path, since nobody has commented it..? Works fine, I wouldn't consider it an "hack".</div>

